            In 1996, as we approached privatisation, the Conservatives adopted a scorched-earth approach. The idea was to sell off a publicly-run industry at any price,
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_211wh' title='Col. 211WH &mdash; HC Deb 13 November 2001 vol 374 c211WH' name='column_211wh' href='#column_211wh' rel='bookmark'>211WH</a>
